News and publications related to European media policy, external relations, Eastern Partnership, Brexit negotiations etc on AEJ website www.aej.org and various national websites e.g. wee.aej-uk.org; 
Two-day Seminar co-organised by AEJ and European Parliament in Brussels in March 2017 with panel debates and presentations on 'future of Europe', 'Brexit', 'fake news and quality media' etc 
AEJ international Congress in Vilnius, Lithuania, 16-19 November 1917: opening speech by Lithuanian vice foreign minister Darius Skusevicius; panel debates on fake news and propaganda, media pluralism and fact-checking, online harassment of women journalists, merits and demerits of data journalism etc
